<section id='sec-11' class='block'>
<div class='act'><span class='act-num'>— Scene XI</span><span class='act-sep'></span><span class='act-tag'>Artifact 11</span></div><h1 class='sec-h1'><span>Test Strategy &amp; QA Approach</span> <em class='brass'>(Elena — QA Specialist)</em></h1>
<p>Elena defined the test strategy: 55 traceability entries, 83 test cases, with full UC↔code traceability.</p>
<h2 id='sub-11-1' class='sec-h2'><span>11.1 Strategy</span></h2>
<p>Risk-based testing with full UC traceability, prioritizing critical fleet operations (vehicle tracking, contract billing, maintenance alerts) and GDPR compliance validation</p>
<h3 class='sec-h3'>Test Environments (4)</h3>
<table class='tbl'>
<thead><tr>
<th><strong>Env</strong></th>
<th><strong>Purpose</strong></th>
<th><strong>Test data</strong></th>
</tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>DEV</strong></td>
<td>Unit tests, developer validation, Flow debugging</td>
<td>Minimal seed data: 10 vehicles, 5 contracts, 3 accounts</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>QA</strong></td>
<td>Integration + regression tests, scheduled automation validation</td>
<td>Anonymized production subset: 150 vehicles, 50 contracts, 30 accounts, 100 maintenance records</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>UAT</strong></td>
<td>Business validation by fleet managers and finance team</td>
<td>Production-like dataset with realistic scenarios (expiring contracts, overdue maintenance, insurance claims)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>PROD</strong></td>
<td>Smoke tests post-deployment, monitoring scheduled jobs</td>
<td>Live data</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
<h3 class='sec-h3'>Tools</h3>
<p>- Salesforce CLI</p>
